summary: This document is an email chain from October 11, 2019, within the FBI's Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit, regarding the approval of travel for agents to conduct victim briefings and interviews in Florida as part of the ongoing Epstein investigation. It details travel logistics and cost estimates for the trip.

events.title: Travel Approval for Epstein Investigation
events.description: The FBI's Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit approves travel for agents to conduct a victim briefing in Miami and subsequent interviews in Miami, West Palm Beach, and Palm Coast, Florida, as part of the ongoing Epstein investigation.

keyFacts: The FBI was actively conducting victim briefings and interviews in Florida in October 2019 as part of the Epstein investigation.
Travel was approved for four agents to attend a victim briefing in Miami and for two agents to conduct follow-up interviews in multiple Florida cities.
The total estimated cost for the investigative travel was $6,263.50.
The correspondence involves the FBI's Crimes Against Children and Human Trafficking Unit (CACHTU) and the Violent Crime Section.
The case number referenced for the travel authorization is 564347.1.
